    "Several recent techniques can be conceptually unified under this p(x|y) framework, showing strong success in aligning GMPDs with specific design objectives.",
    "In this review, we categorize these strategies into two broad classes: (i) train-time methods, which modify the model parameters so that the learned distribution Training can proceed via masked-token prediction, in which the model infers the identity of masked residues, or via autoregressive next-token prediction, where sequences are generated one residue at a time.",
